; The surface is warm and safe, so the grade is warm and only lightly dimmed,
; the headroom sinks less than the mine's, and the same helmet lamp rides the
; player. Same system as the delve, tuned bright.
; The surface is already a lit, warm room, so the helmet lamp is nearly off up
; here — a faint glow, not a personal floodlight. On the bright grade any real
; additive light clips the player to white and eats his detail, so both the
; travel pool and the key light are dialled right down (delve keeps the defaults).
[node name="MineAtmosphere" type="Node" parent="."]
script = ExtResource("9_atmo")
darkness = Color(0.72, 0.64, 0.55, 1)
lantern_energy = 0.45
lantern_scale = 3.2
key_energy = 0.28
key_scale = 1.4
top_shadow = 0.35
dust_amount = 10
haze_amount = 3
vignette_strength = 0.42

[node name="PickupFeedback" type="Node" parent="."]
